# HKHeartRateMotionContext.notSet

**Case**

A value indicating that the user’s activity level could not be determined.

## Declaration

```swift
case notSet
```

## Discussion

This value is identical to the sample’s metadata not containing a [doc://com.apple.healthkit/documentation/HealthKit/HKMetadataKeyHeartRateMotionContext] key.

## Motion Contextes

- **HKHeartRateMotionContext.active**: A value indicating that the user was in motion during the heart rate sample.
- **HKHeartRateMotionContext.sedentary**: A value indicating that the user has been still for at least 5 minutes prior to the heart rate sample.
